headlines.description: — Toronto Raptors coach Darko Rajakovic promised his players a tasty reward when they finally strung together a three-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Scottie Barnes records his 4th triple-double of the season, Raptors beat Pacers 130-122

events.name: Detroit Pistons at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson missed a 3-pointer, eventually got the ball back and passed it to Josh Hart for the go-ahead basket.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hart makes go-ahead basket after chaotic possession as Knicks beat Pistons 113-111

headlines.description: — Dennis Schroder scored 18 points, Dorian Finney-Smith added 13 points and nine rebounds, and the Brooklyn Nets cruised past the Memphis Grizzlies 111-86 on Monday night, giving Kevin Ollie his first win as an NBA coach.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets beat Grizzlies 111-86 for interim coach Kevin Ollie's first win

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo scored 28 points, Jaime Jaquez Jr. added 26 and the short-handed Miami Heat beat the Sacramento Kings 121-110 on Monday night for their fourth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: The short-handed Heat beat the Kings 121-110 for their 4th straight win
